		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />In <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?p=11307#11307" class="postlink">this post</a>, Bregalad called the Nintendo Revolution console's airmouse controller "horrible". Does any other video game console have a mouse-equivalent pointing device that is not horrible? Does any PC or console allow for up to four distinct pointing devices, one per player?

		

